Look at what hatched! 😱 Yucatan box turtles (Terrapene yucatan) are a very unique and rare box turtle that only occurs on the Yucatán peninsula in Mexico. The males develop amazing, atypical coloration in the form of blues, yellows and even bright white. Some will feature pink hues, as well. Like other box turtles we are more familiar with in the United States, Yucatáns prefer moist forests and live a mostly terrestrial life. They are omnivores and prefer to consume fallen fruit, invertebrates and mushrooms.

Baby turtles galore!! It’s that time of year again when we get to release hatchling diamondback terrapins that have been spending all summer inside their eggs, incubating. Our project @terrapinconservationinitiative was founded in 2017 and since then we have successfully released thousands of hatchlings! It’s critical for them to get back to the salt marsh as quickly as possible so they can imprint on the environment and the specifics it offers the turtles including appropriate food items. As babies, these terrapins play a vital role in the salt marsh ecosystem. So far we’ve let go 63 perfect babies this season. Good luck little ones!

Biologist Discovers What Tortoises Say While Mating 🤣

Male tortoises of various species emit sounds during breeding efforts. Females can actually mimic this during territorial displays. The sounds are often high pitched squeaks or grunts, even “quacks”, dependent on species, and the male gapes his mouth while doing this. People tend to find this rather comical as breeding can occur quite frequently, especially under captive management. Now, run a recorded clip of it through a captions generator and the results are even funnier! 😉🤣

*The tortoises in this clip are rescued sulcata tortoises. Females will lay eggs even without a male present, much like chickens do. Since this species is so overbred & overrun in the mid-Atlantic & northeast USA (places they cannot survive outdoors year-round) we feed the eggs to our lizards instead of allowing them to develop and hatch. This way we can offer a home to more unwanted tortoises without adding to the growing issue.

Look at both of us in that first pic…we look like babies! Seems like yesterday we were sitting on our old kitchen floor with you and Robyn, as you told Casey and I stories about the Irwin’s and so much more. In the last couple of years we were fortunate to spend more time together. Laughing, telling stories, filming again and more. This time together with you, Lori and the crew will be cherished, always. You created an empire for the entire reptile community and beyond. You turned dreams into realities and showed us that we should never shy away from what we are truly passionate about.

I often wondered if you were even slightly aware of the magnitude of influence you have on us all. Sure, I’d talk to you like a friend, because simply put, we are friends. We’d sit down, talk shit, talk reptiles, geek out over Jaws toys, talk about life in general….but I’d always wonder if you really knew what you mean to the community, even in times of darkness. I’d think, “He’s crazy if he doubts for one second that he isn’t cherished by literally everyone.” 

Because of you, I’ve gotten the privilege to be around your team to where I now consider them family. Your influence and contagious positivity are instilled in them and they’ll carry the torch higher than you could ever imagine, all because they love you, trust you and know you, for real. You paved their way and lovingly set the stage for them. I’m blessed to be able to call them my friends, too. 

I only just got home from spending time out there to help out any way I could. We accomplished a lot and although we laughed hard, It was tough at times. But, laughter is so crucial, even when your heart is breaking. That’s because a breaking heart is a funny thing. It gives you the courage to be real and as Golda Meir once said, “Those who do not know how to weep with their whole heart do not know how to laugh either.” 

Brian, thank you, for the passion, the family, the friendship, the love, and the indestructible empire you have given us. 

I told you once and I’ll proudly say it again…

To me, you are Walt Disney. 

Chris
